Installing PGpool-II
1>Go to the below URL
https://pgpool.net/mediawiki/index.php/Downloads
2>As per postgres version select the compatible version and download
3>Now to install this download WSL
https://ubuntu.com/desktop/wsl
4>now install this
5>now open WSL
6>type below commands
•	Go to the directory
o	cd /path/to/downloaded/file
•	Extract it
o	tar -xzf pgpool-II-4.5.3.tar.gz
•	Install dependencies (ONE TIME, may go online)
o	cd pgpool-II-4.5.3
•	After this step, Pgpool itself will be installed ONLY from your local files
•	Configure using your local PostgreSQL
o	./configure
•	If PostgreSQL is in a custom path:
o	./configure --with-pgsql=/usr/lib/postgres
•	Build and install
o	make
o	sudo make install
•	Verify
o	pgpool --version

